                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Taylor</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Canadian Government in a note dated June 28,<note n="19" xml:id="d733fn19">Not
                        printed.</note> copy of which is being sent to you by mail, expresses some
                    doubt as to feasibility of setting up continuing body “at a time when the League
                    of Nations is endeavoring to coordinate and centralize existing refugee
                    organizations and to break down the differentiations between the various classes
                    or groups of refugees.” Canadian Government also states that points (2) and (3)
                    of agenda raise difficult problems under Canadian immigration laws.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
